cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.MM

This paper deals with the challenges of providing reliability guarantees to a massive number of M2M devices in LTE systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes a proactive approach to deal with the massive arrivals, which involves resource allocation and estimation. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper deals with security issues related to M2M communications, which could place it in the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) category. Finally, the paper discusses the impact of the proposed approach on multimedia applications, which could place it in the cs.MM (Multimedia) category.
